{"title_page": "Anastasia Papadopoulou", "text_new": "{{BLP sources|date=February 2017}}\n\n{{Infobox football biography\n|name           = Anastasia Papadopoulou\n|image          =\n|caption        =\n|fullname       =\n|birth_date     = {{birth date and age|1986|7|1|df=yes}}\n|birth_place    = [[Greece]]\n|height         =\n|position       = [[Forward (association football)|Forward]]\n|youthyears1    =\n|youthclubs1    =\n|years1         = 2004\n|clubs1         = [[Kavala 86]]\n|caps1          =\n|goals1         =\n|years2         =\n|clubs2         =\n|caps2          =\n|goals2         =\n|totalcaps      =\n|totalgoals     =\n|nationalyears1 = 2004\n|nationalteam1  =[[Greece women's national football team|Greece]]\n|nationalcaps1  = 34 {{tooltip|(?)|Before the 2004 Summer Olympics}}\n|nationalgoals1 = 4\n}}\n'''Anastasia Papadopoulou ''' (born {{birth date|1986|7|1|df=yes}}) is a female Greek [[association football|football]] [[Forward (association football)|forward]]. She was part of the [[Greece women's national football team]]  at the [[Football at the 2004 Summer Olympics \u2013 Women's tournament|2004 Summer Olympics]]. \nOn club level she played for [[Kavala 86]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.fifa.com/tournaments/archive/womensolympic/athens2004/teams/team=1884896/index.html |title=Olympic Women's Football Tournaments Athens 2004 \u2013 Squad List: Greece (GRE) |publisher=[[FIFA]] |accessdate=2 October 2015 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150906013026/http://www.fifa.com/tournaments/archive/womensolympic/athens2004/teams/team%3D1884896/index.html |archivedate=6 September 2015 |df=dmy-all }}</ref>\n\n==See also==\n* [[Greece at the 2004 Summer Olympics]]\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{cite Sports-Reference |url=https://www.sports-reference.com/olympics/athletes/pa/anastasia-papadopoulou-1.html |title=Anastasia Papadopoulou |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160307212640/http://www.sports-refere